data.protoText: Prepare Pneumacult Ex-Plus Growth Medium：Thaw the 50X supplement at room temperature. Mix by gently inverting the bottle.
Add the contents of the 50X supplement to a bottle of Ex-Plus Basal medium.
Add 0.5 mL of hydrocortisone stock solution
Sterile fi lter with a 0.22 mm vacuum fi ltration bottle and store at 4 °C for up to one month.
Prepare Pneumacult ALI Differentiation Medium
Complete base medium
Maintenance medium
add 1 bottle of 10X Supplement (thawed overnight at 4 °C) to a bottle of ALI base medium.

start with 100 mL of complete base medium, add 1 vial of 100X Maintenance supplement (1 mL), 0.2 mL of heparin solution, and 0.5 mL of hydrocortisone stock solution. Sterile fi lter with a 0.22 mm vacuum fi ltration bottle
Thawing Cryopreserved Cells
Warm Pneumacult Ex-Plus growth medium to 37 °C and prepare materials prior to obtaining a vial of cells from cryostorage.
Remove vial from liquid nitrogen (wearing eye protection) and thaw in 37 °C water bath (1-2 min).
Transfer the thawed cells from the cryovial into the growth medium using a P1000 pipette and gently mix by inverting 10 times.
Pellet cells via centrifugation at 1,000 x g for 4 minutes at room temperature in centrifuge
Add 24 mL of growth medium to a 50 mL conical tube
Carefully aspirate the supernatant.
Gently resuspend the cells in pre-warmed growth medium and transfer to a flask
Distribute cell suspension on the dish through a combination of gentle rocking and swirling of the dish for approximately 15 seconds.
Place in a tissue culture incubator overnight
Check cells the following day for attachment to the dish. Aspirate and replace medium.
Passaging and Expansion of pHBEC
Pre-warm Pneumacult ALI growth medium and DPBS in a 37 °C water bath and a trypsin aliquot at room temperature for approximately 30 minutes.
Add trypsin-EDTA solution and place in a tissue culture incubator for 2-3 minutes.
When approximately 80-90% of the cells are detached , add a half volume of SBTI to the flask, pipet up the trypsin/SBTI mixture, and rinse the vessel bottom.
Transfer the cells to a sterile centrifuge tube
Pellet cells at 200-600 x g for 5 minutes at room temperature in a centrifuge with a swinging bucket rotor

Aspirate the supernatant. Note the size of the cell pellet before tapping the tube to break up the pellet. Ideally, the pellet should be resuspended in a volume of medium that will yield a cell density of 1.0x106 cells/mL. Triturate the cells with a serological pipet to create a homogeneous suspension
Transfer a 10 mL aliquot of the cell suspension to a hemocytometer and count the cells.
Adjust the number of cells to approximately 1.0x106/mL
Change the medium every other day until cells reach approximately 70% confluence.
Differentiation of pHBEC Cultures at ALI
Prepare a volume and dilution of cell suspension
If seeding 12 24mm inserts at 3.0x105 cells per insert then prepare sufficient cell suspension for seeding 14 inserts to allow for volume lost during handling.

If your cells were resuspended at a concentration of 1.0x106/mL, then you would add 4.2 mL of the cell suspension to 6.3 mL of additional medium to get the desired plating density (3.0x105/0.75 mL added to each insert)
Allow cells to adhere to Transwell inserts for 16-24 hours
After the adhesion period, aspirate medium to remove nonadherent cells
Add fresh Pneumacult Ex-Plus growth medium in the apical compartment.
Continue to grow in Pneumacult Ex-Plus growth medium until the cells are confluent.
Once cells are confluent, withdraw the apical medium and replace the basolateral medium with Pneumacult ALI differentiation medium.
Replace the Pneumacult ALI differentiation medium in the basolateral compartment every 48 hours
Wash the apical surface with DPBS at least once per week
Determine the number of inserts to be seeded and adjust cell density and volume as outlined in the table below. STEMCELL recommends 0.5 x 105 cells/cm2.
Cryopreservation of pHBEC
Pellet cells again at 200-600 x g for 4 minutes at room temperature in centrifuge with a swinging bucket rotor.
Resuspend the pellet in CryStor10 Freezing Medium at a minimum of 1.0x106 cells/mL
Gently mix by pipetting. Transfer 1.0 mL of the cell suspension to each cryovial.
Place cryovials in a Mr. Frosty freezing container (fi lled to indicated line with isopropyl alcohol) and place in a -80 °C freezer overnight.
Transfer the frozen vials in liquid nitrogen storage.
